article.headline: Gonzaga 74, San Diego 64
article.story: SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Micah Downs scored a career-high 20 points to lead Gonzaga to a 74-64 win over San Diego Monday, clinching the Bulldogs' seventh straight West Coast Conference regular-season title. Jeremy Pargo had 15 points and David Pendergraft added 11 for Gonzaga (21-10, 11-3 West Coast), which finished the regular season one game ahead of Santa Clara, which lost 89-82 in overtime to Pepperdine. Downs scored 13 of his points during an 18-5 run in the second half that put the Zags ahead 60-50 with 9:22 left in the game. Ross DeRogatis scored 22 points, including six 3-pointers, for San Diego (16-13, 6-8). Gyno Pomare scored 12 points and Ray Murdock added 11 for the Toreros.
